body:
### Description

I have a Blazor WASM project and using SkiaSharp SKCanvasView with styling on the canvas that is setting height to 100%. But the SKCanvasView takes some random height that is less than 100%.

I am using nuget package: SkiaSharp.Views.Blazor, ver. 3.119.0


### Code

Link to a GitHub repository showing issue:
https://github.com/skanva/TestSS

Here is the relevant test code
```
@page "/"
@using SkiaSharp
@using SkiaSharp.Views.Blazor

<PageTitle>Test</PageTitle>

<div class="top-container">
    <div class="canvas-container">
        <SKCanvasView  OnPaintSurface="OnPaintSurface" />
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    .top-container {
        flex: 1 1 auto;
        width: 100%;
        min-height: 100%;
        border: 1px solid red;
        padding: 1rem;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
    }

    .canvas-container {
        flex: 1;
        background-color: #90ee90;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
    }

    .canvas-container canvas {
        padding: 0;
        margin: 0;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
    }
</style>

@code {
    private void OnPaintSurface(SKPaintSurfaceEventArgs e)
    {
        var canvas = e.Surface.Canvas;

        canvas.Clear(SKColors.Blue);

        using var paint = new SKPaint
            {
                Color = SKColors.Yellow,
                IsAntialias = true
            };

        SKFont font = new SKFont(SKTypeface.Default, 32);

        canvas.DrawText($"{e.RawInfo.Width} : {e.RawInfo.Height}", 20, 50, font, paint);
    }
}
```



### Expected Behavior

The canvas should fill 100% of the area.

### Actual Behavior

The height of the canvas never fills 100% of the area.

The Skia canvas only fills the blue area.

It should extend to cover the green area.

